textRun.content: Entero is looking to evolve its relationship with chemists from a transactional supply chain model into a value-generating, digitally enabled partnership. In this first phase, Think41 will help Entero design and implement a Progressive Web App (PWA) and WhatsApp-based experience that chemists can use to serve their retail customers directly.
Increase chemist revenue by enabling online and WhatsApp-based customer  manufacturers, chemists, and retail customers
Provide tools like refill reminders, substitute recommendations, and digital storefronts to improve conversion, retention, and repeat orders
By enabling this manufacturer-to-chemist-to-customer flow, Entero positions itself as the digital enabler for its chemist ecosystem.

The estimated story points  and duration are indicative and based on the current understanding of scope and requirements. These are subject to change during detailed planning, sprint grooming, or based on evolving needs and feedback during the project execution.
Timelines and delivery commitments are contingent on timely availability of inputs, approvals, and access from the client team. Delays in these may impact overall delivery and incentive eligibility.
All estimates and plans assume a standard agile development process with bi-weekly sprints, a single product owner on the client side, and clear acceptance criteria for stories.
Sprint-based incentives (P1 to P8) will be paid out
proportionally based on the story points completed
vs. planned for each sprint group. These are not all-or-nothing payouts and will scale with actual delivery.
Invoicing will be done based on the number of story points executed in each sprint.
The team will be available full-time for the duration of the engagement. Any deviation (planned leave, holidays) will be communicated in advance.
Billing will occur monthly based on the story points, as per the agreed story point cost.
Timely access to ERP, Entero Direct, and relevant systems or APIs.
Designation of a SPOC for requirement clarifications, sprint reviews, and issuer solution.
Prompt feedback during sprint cycles to avoid delays in development or testing.
Think41 will be provided access to development and test environments as needed.
Any delays due to lack of access or dependency resolution on the client’s side may impact timelines but will not affect billing.
Any third-party API or cloud service costs are to be borne by the client.
Think41 will assist in cost estimation and optimization strategies but will not be responsible for these expenses.
The project will follow Agile methodologies, with iterative development and regular feedback loops.
Burn down charts are shared after each sprint to provide visibility and enable progress tracking effectively.
Invoice is raised after every two sprints based on no. of story points actually completed vs Estimated.

Any change requests will be estimated in story points. If the effort required is within the  limit of the planned capacity, it will be absorbed without additional cost. Requests exceeding this threshold will be charged based on the per story point rate.
Think41 will provide a dedicated pod of engineers working full-time.
A Single Point of Contact (SPOC) from Entero’s side is required to facilitate communication and decision-making.
By signing below, both parties acknowledge and agree to the terms and conditions outlined in this Agreement.
